From 705afd80793536bae259d61ed52c01be969ca8d2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "Keane (via Claude)" <keane@cybershield.local>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 08:25:05 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] security: move quiz answer validation server-side

- Add Cloud Functions validateAnswer / validateAnswersBatch that grade
  answers against a server-only answerKeys collection (Admin SDK), guarded
  by App Check + auth.
- Remove correctIndex/explanation from the client-facing Question model
  and from Firestore question docs (migrated to answerKeys via
  functions/src/scripts/migrateAnswerKeys.ts).
- Firestore rules: block all client writes to quizResults and all client
  read/write to answerKeys.
- Online: QuizViewModel calls validateAnswer immediately for instant
  feedback, using only the server's verdict.
- Offline: answers are cached locally (selectedIndex only) and graded
  later via validateAnswersBatch once connectivity returns; quiz
  completion is marked provisional and XP/badge/certificate awarding is
  deferred until every answer is graded.
- Room schema: quiz_results gains questionId/selectedIndex/explanation,
  isCorrect is now nullable pending server grading.
